<TITLE> Army officer dies, 2 other injured in Syl catt </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sylhet, June 28 (bdnews24.com)An army officer died and two others were seriously injured on Sunday when a recoilless rifle shell exploded at the training ground of Jalalabad Cantonment of Sylhet, police said. Lieutenant Mainul Haque, 23, of 17 East Bengal Regiment, who died on the spot . Lieutenant Towheed and Sergeant Maniruzzaman, instructor of School of Infantry & Tactics An army helicopter rushed to Dhaka carrying the two injured. Sub-inspector Fakhrul Alam Badal of Sylhet Kotowali Police Station said the heavy recoilless rifle shell went off at around 1pm during a training programme. Lieutenant Mainul died on the spot." Fakhrul said he visited the spot in the afternoon after when he was called in by the army officials. bdne
